Hickson is believed to have known and regularly associated with the victim, according to the ABC.  

It's reported the victim had recently moved to Cairns for work, and had been  returning to Napier every three months to be with his wife and children.

Cairns Regional Crime Coordinator Detective Inspector Bruno Asnicar says information received about seven days ago led detectives to believe the dead man may have been missing and had possibly met with foul play.

'It's important to remember that he wasn't reported missing,' he told reporters in Cairns on Thursday. 'We believed there were some suspicious circumstances around the potential this guy might be missing and we've launched it from there.'

